#: templates/manuals/r1.html:197
msgid "#1 Check WiFi Coverage"
msgstr "#1 Verificar Cobertura WiFi"

msgid ""
"\n"
"                          <h5>Ensure that good 2.4GHz WiFi signal will "
"reach the device area all the time.</h5>\n"
"\n"
"                            <p class=\"alert alert-info\">\n"
"                              Optimal Wi-Fi signal strength is crucial "
"for device performance.\n"
"                              Before installation, use a mobile app (WiFi"
" Analyzer) with a 3dBm reference antenna to measure the\n"
"                              signal at the location. Ensure it's between"
" <b>-30 dBm</b> and <b>-78 dBm</b>.\n"
"                              After connecting, regularly verify this on "
"the device's webpage.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            <p class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n"
"                              If WiFi signal strength is weak consider "
"add WiFi range extenders.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                          <h5>Asegúrese de que una buena señal de WiFi de"
" 2.4GHz llegue al área del dispositivo en todo momento.</h5>\n"
"\n"
"                            <p class=\"alert alert-info\" >\n"
"                              La intensidad de la señal Wi-Fi óptima es "
"crucial para el rendimiento del dispositivo.\n"
"                              Antes de la instalación, use una aplicación"
" móvil (WiFi Analyzer) con una antena de referencia de 3dBm para medir la"
"\n"
"                              señal en el lugar. Asegúrese de que esté "
"entre <b>-30 dBm</b> y <b>-78 dBm</b>.\n"
"                              Después de conectar, verifique regularmente"
" esto en la página web del dispositivo.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            <p class=\"alert alert-warning\" >\n"
"                              Si la intensidad de la señal WiFi es débil,"
" considere agregar extensores de alcance WiFi.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:221
msgid "#2 Pump and Safety Requirements "
msgstr "#2 Requisitos del Motor de Agua y Seguridad"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:226
msgid ""
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                              <h5>Pump Requirements</h5>\n"
"                              Ensure the pump's power consumption does "
"not exceed <b>10 amps</b> to prevent potential damage or system overload."
"\n"
"                              This translates to a maximum of <b>1200 "
"W</b> for a 120 V system and <b>2200 W</b> for a 220 V system.\n"
"                              Exceeding these limits may compromise "
"system safety and functionality.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-info\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                            <h5>Power Requirements</h5>\n"
"                            The device requires a power input of AC 120V "
"or 220V, 50/60 Hz, with a single-phase connection and neutral line.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                            <h5>Safety Requirements</h5>\n"
"                              Since this is an experimental device, the "
"user is responsible for ensuring safe installation and operation.\n"
"                              Make sure the system has a thermal breaker "
"for protection and avoid placing it near\n"
"                              flammable materials. The user should also "
"monitor the device regularly to ensure it\n"
"                              operates correctly and safely.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"                          "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                              <h5>Requisitos del Motor de Agua</h5>\n"
"                              Asegúrate de que el consumo de energía del "
"motor de agua no exceda <b>10 amperios</b> para evitar daños o sobrecarga"
" del sistema.\n"
"                              Esto equivale a un máximo de <b>1200 W</b> "
"para un sistema de 120 V y <b>2200 W</b> para un sistema de 220 V.\n"
"                              Exceder estos límites puede comprometer la "
"seguridad y funcionalidad del sistema.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-info\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                            <h5>Requisitos de Energía</h5>\n"
"                            El dispositivo requiere una entrada de "
"energía de CA 120V o 220V, 50/60 Hz, con una conexión monofásica y línea "
"neutra.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"\n"
"                          <div class=\"ms-1 my-3 alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                            <h5>Requisitos de Seguridad</h5>\n"
"                              Dado que este es un dispositivo "
"experimental, el usuario es responsable de garantizar una instalación y "
"operación seguras.\n"
"                              Asegúrate de que el sistema tenga un "
"interruptor térmico para protección y evita colocarlo cerca\n"
"                              de materiales inflamables. El usuario "
"también debe monitorear el dispositivo regularmente para asegurarse de "
"que\n"
"                              funcione correctamente y de manera segura.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"                          "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:253
msgid "#3 Installing the Controller "
msgstr "#3 Instalación del Controlador"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:263
msgid ""
"\n"
"                              <h5>Device Connection Instructions</h5>\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>1. Select "
"Proper Cables:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 Use cables that can handle the amperage "
"of the pump (up to 10 amps) to ensure safe operation.\n"
"                                 Make sure the cables are rated for the "
"required power load.</p>\n"
"\n"
"                              <div class=\"my-3 ms-1\"><strong>2. AC "
"Input Connections:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       <strong>Identify the AC input "
"wires:</strong> You will need to identify the <strong>Line "
"(Live)</strong>, <strong>Neutral</strong>, and <strong>Ground</strong> "
"wires coming from the power source.<li>\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       <strong>Connect the wires to AC-"
"IN:</strong>\n"
"                                        Connect the <strong>Line</strong>"
" (Live) wire to the <strong>Line (L)</strong> terminal,\n"
"                                        the <strong>Neutral</strong> wire"
" to the <strong>Neutral (N)</strong> terminal, and the "
"<strong>Ground</strong> wire to the\n"
"                                       <strong>Ground (G)</strong> "
"terminal on the device's <strong>AC-IN</strong> section. Make sure each "
"wire is properly secured\n"
"                                       to avoid any loose connections.\n"
"                                     </li>\n"
"                                 </ul>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                              <div class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>3. AC "
"Output Connections:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       <strong>Connect to the "
"pump:</strong> In the <strong>AC-Out</strong> section of the device, "
"repeat the process\n"
"                                       by connecting the "
"<strong>Line</strong> wire to the <strong>Line (L)</strong> terminal,\n"
"                                       the <strong>Neutral</strong> wire "
"to the <strong>Neutral (N)</strong> terminal,\n"
"                                       and the <strong>Ground</strong> "
"wire to the <strong>Ground (G)</strong> terminal.<li>\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       Make sure the connections are "
"correct, secure, and tight to ensure reliable operation of the pump.<li>"
"\n"
"                                 </ul>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                            <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>4. Mount the "
"Device:</strong><br>\n"
"                              Use the <strong>mount points</strong> on "
"the device to securely attach it to a wall\n"
"                              or other stable surface. Ensure the "
"mounting location is dry, accessible, and allows for proper ventilation "
"around the device.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\"><strong>5. Verify "
"Connections:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 Before turning the device on, double-"
"check all connections to ensure they are correctly placed and there are "
"no errors. Incorrect wiring could lead to malfunctions or damage to the "
"pump.</p>\n"
"                           "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                              <h5>Instrucciones de Conexión del "
"Dispositivo</h5>\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>1. "
"Selecciona los Cables Adecuados:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 Usa cables que puedan manejar el "
"amperaje del motor de agua (hasta 10 amperios) para garantizar una "
"operación segura.\n"
"                                 Asegúrate de que los cables estén "
"clasificados para la carga de energía requerida.</p>\n"
"\n"
"                              <div class=\"my-3 ms-1\" ><strong>2. "
"Conexiones de Entrada de CA:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\" >\n"
"                                       <strong>Identifica los cables de "
"entrada de CA:</strong> Deberás identificar los cables de <strong>Línea "
"(Fase)</strong>, <strong>Neutro</strong> y <strong>Tierra</strong> que "
"provienen de la fuente de energía.</li>\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\" >\n"
"                                       <strong>Conecta los cables a AC-"
"IN:</strong>\n"
"                                        Conecta el cable de <strong>Línea"
" (Fase)</strong> al terminal <strong>Línea (L)</strong>,\n"
"                                        el cable de "
"<strong>Neutro</strong> al terminal <strong>Neutro (N)</strong>, y el "
"cable de <strong>Tierra</strong> al\n"
"                                       terminal <strong>Tierra "
"(G)</strong> en la sección <strong>AC-IN</strong> del dispositivo. "
"Asegúrate de que cada cable esté bien sujeto\n"
"                                       para evitar conexiones flojas.\n"
"                                     </li>\n"
"                                 </ul>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                              <div class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>3. "
"Conexiones de Salida de CA:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 mt-3\">\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       <strong>Conecta el motor de agua: "
"</strong> En la sección <strong>AC-Out</strong> del dispositivo, repite "
"el proceso\n"
"                                       conectando el cable de "
"<strong>Línea</strong> al terminal <strong>Línea (L)</strong>,\n"
"                                       el cable de "
"<strong>Neutro</strong> al terminal <strong>Neutro (N)</strong>,\n"
"                                       y el cable de "
"<strong>Tierra</strong> al terminal <strong>Tierra (G)</strong>.</li>\n"
"                                     <li class=\"list-group-item list-"
"group-item-action list-group-item-primary\">\n"
"                                       Asegúrate de que las conexiones "
"sean correctas, seguras y estén bien ajustadas para garantizar un "
"funcionamiento confiable del motor de agua.</li>\n"
"                                 </ul>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                            <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>4. Monta el "
"Dispositivo:</strong><br>\n"
"                              Usa los <strong>puntos de montaje</strong> "
"del dispositivo para fijarlo de manera segura a una pared\n"
"                              o superficie estable. Asegúrate de que la "
"ubicación de montaje esté seca, sea accesible y permita una ventilación "
"adecuada alrededor del dispositivo.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2 ms-1\" ><strong>5. Verifica"
" las Conexiones:</strong><br>\n"
"                                 Antes de encender el dispositivo, revisa"
" todas las conexiones para asegurarte de que estén correctamente "
"colocadas y no haya errores. Un cableado incorrecto podría causar fallos "
"o daños en el motor de agua.</p>\n"
"                           "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:312
msgid "#4 Configure Wi-Fi connection for the device. "
msgstr "#4 Configura la conexión Wi-Fi para el dispositivo."

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:317
msgid ""
"\n"
"                          <p>In this step, configure the device to "
"connect to your local internet WiFi network</p>\n"
"                          <div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n"
"                            To enjoy all the features of this device, "
"you'll need to <a href=\"/register\" target=\"_blank\">create a free "
"account</a>\n"
"                            using your email address. <br>\n"
"                            This will allow you to link the device to "
"your profile\n"
"                            and personalize your settings.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"                          <h5>Steps:</h5>\n"
"                          <ul class=\"list-group ms-1\">\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                                <b>1)</b> Connect the device to an AC "
"power source and switch the <a href=\"#collapsePartOne\"><b>Manual/Smart "
"Switch</b></a>\n"
"                                to the <b>ON</b> position. This will "
"power on the LEDs and screen, enabling the smart features\n"
"                                of the pump controller. Ensure the WiFi "
"antenna is securely connected to the <b>Pump Controller</b>.\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>2)</b> Using a cellphone, search and "
"connect to a 2.4GHz WiFi network named <b>WaterLevelProSetup</b> with "
"credentials/password: <b>1122334455</b>\n"
"                              <div class=\"alert alert-warning mt-2\">\n"
"                                If the network name doesn't show or "
"disappears quickly, check <b>AC</b> power input or press the WiFi Reset "
"button at <b>Pump Controller</b>.\n"
"                                <div class=\"alert alert-info mt-3\">\n"
"                                  To reset the WiFi, press the <b>WiFi "
"Reset</b> button 5 consecutive times.\n"
"                                </div>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>3) Enter your local WiFi auth info.</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                After completing step <b>2)</b>, a "
"Captive Portal will appear on your cellphone. This will guide you to a "
"webpage where\n"
"                                you can select the desired Wi-Fi network "
"and enter its credentials. You will also be prompted to enter an\n"
"                                email address to link the device to your "
"existing account.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                If the Captive Portal don't load "
"automatically use this url\n"
"                                <a href=\"http://192.168.4.1/\" "
"target=\"_blank\">http://192.168.4.1/</a> to load it manually from "
"cellphone.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>4) Check your device is online</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                Reconnect your cellphone to the internet "
"and log in to your account. If everything\n"
"                                  was successful, after <b>2 minute</b>, "
"you will see the new device listed in your account with an "
"<b>\"Online\"</b> status.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                If the device does not show online after "
"<b>2 minute</b>, try reconnecting the power source or repeating\n"
"                                the entire process after pressing the "
"<b>WiFi Reset</b> button 5 consecutive times on the device.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                          </ul>\n"
"                          "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                          <p>En este paso, configura el dispositivo para "
"que se conecte a tu red WiFi local de internet.</p>\n"
"                          <div class=\"alert alert-info\" >\n"
"                            Para disfrutar de todas las funciones de este"
" dispositivo, necesitarás <a href=\"/register\" target=\"_blank\" >crear "
"una cuenta gratuita</a>\n"
"                            usando tu dirección de correo electrónico. "
"<br>\n"
"                            Esto te permitirá vincular el dispositivo a "
"tu perfil\n"
"                            y personalizar tus configuraciones.\n"
"                          </div>\n"
"                          <h5>Pasos:</h5>\n"
"                          <ul class=\"list-group ms-1\" >\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                                <b>1)</b> Conecta el dispositivo a una "
"fuente de alimentación de CA y cambia el <a href=\"#collapsePartOne\" "
"><b>Interruptor Manual/Inteligente</b></a>\n"
"                                a la posición <b>ON</b>. Esto encenderá "
"los LEDs y la pantalla, habilitando las funciones inteligentes\n"
"                                del controlador del motor de agua. "
"Asegúrate de que la antena WiFi esté conectada firmemente al "
"<b>Controlador del Motor de Agua</b>.\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\" >\n"
"                              <b>2)</b> Usando un celular, busca y "
"conéctate a una red WiFi de 2.4GHz llamada <b>WaterLevelProSetup</b> con "
"la contraseña: <b>1122334455</b>\n"
"                              <div class=\"alert alert-warning mt-2\">\n"
"                                Si el nombre de la red no aparece o "
"desaparece rápidamente, verifica la entrada de <b>CA</b> o presiona el "
"botón de Reinicio WiFi en el <b>Controlador del Motor de Agua</b>.\n"
"                                <div class=\"alert alert-info mt-3\" >\n"
"                                  Para reiniciar el WiFi, presiona el "
"botón <b>Reinicio WiFi</b> 5 veces consecutivas.\n"
"                                </div>\n"
"                              </div>\n"
"\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\" >\n"
"                              <b>3) Ingresa la información de "
"autenticación de tu WiFi local.</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                Después de completar el paso <b>2)</b>, "
"aparecerá un Portal Cautivo en tu celular. Esto te guiará a una página "
"web donde\n"
"                                podrás seleccionar la red Wi-Fi deseada e"
" ingresar sus credenciales. También se te pedirá que ingreses una\n"
"                                dirección de correo electrónico para "
"vincular el dispositivo a tu cuenta existente.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                Si el Portal Cautivo no se carga "
"automáticamente, usa esta URL\n"
"                                <a href=\"http://192.168.4.1/\" "
"target=\"_blank\">http://192.168.4.1/</a> para cargarlo manualmente desde"
" tu celular.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                            <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-"
"action\">\n"
"                              <b>4) Verifica que tu dispositivo esté en "
"línea</b>\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-2\">\n"
"                                Reconecta tu celular a internet e inicia "
"sesión en tu cuenta de <b>Waterlevel.Pro</b>. Si todo\n"
"                                  fue exitoso, después de <b>2 "
"minutos</b>, verás el nuevo dispositivo listado en tu cuenta con un "
"estado <b>\"En línea\"</b>.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                Si el dispositivo no aparece en línea "
"después de <b>2 minutos</b>, intenta reconectar la fuente de alimentación"
" o repetir\n"
"                                todo el proceso después de presionar el "
"botón <b>Reinicio WiFi</b> 5 veces consecutivas en el dispositivo.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                            </li>\n"
"                          </ul>\n"
"                          "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:374
msgid "#5 Smart Settings "
msgstr "#5 Configuración Inteligente"

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:427
msgid "#6 Manual Mode - <b> Manual/Smart Switch</b> "
msgstr "#6 Modo Manual - <b> Interruptor Manual/Inteligente</b> "

#: templates/manuals/r1.html:432
msgid ""
"\n"
"                            <h5>Using the <b>Manual/Smart Switch</b> "
"Button</h5>\n"
"                            <p class=\"ms-2 my-3\">\n"
"                                The physical <a "
"href=\"#collapsePartOne\"><b>Manual/Smart Switch</b></a> button on\n"
"                                the pump controller allows you to operate"
" the pump manually, functioning like a simple\n"
"                                switch that turns the pump on without "
"requiring internet or smart features. To enable this,\n"
"                                move the <a "
"href=\"#collapsePartOne\"><b>Manual/Smart Switch</b></a> to the OFF "
"position.\n"
"                                The LEDs and screen will turn off, but "
"the pump will start running.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            <div class=\"alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\">\n"
"                                Before switching to <b>Manual Mode</b>, "
"verify that the pump is not <b>ON</b> while in <b>Smart Mode</b>.\n"
"                                Use the web UI control to check its "
"status. Confirm that the green indicator <b>LED</b> is off before "
"proceeding.\n"
"                            </div>\n"
"                            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                            <h5>Uso del botón <b>Interruptor "
"Manual/Inteligente</b></h5>\n"
"                            <p class=\"ms-2 my-3\" >\n"
"                                El botón físico <a "
"href=\"#collapsePartOne\" ><b>Interruptor Manual/Inteligente</b></a> en\n"
"                                el controlador del motor de agua te "
"permite operar el motor de agua manualmente, funcionando como un\n"
"                                interruptor simple que enciende el motor "
"de agua sin necesidad de internet o funciones inteligentes. Para "
"habilitar esto,\n"
"                                mueve el <a href=\"#collapsePartOne\" "
"><b>Interruptor Manual/Inteligente</b></a> a la posición OFF.\n"
"                                Los LEDs y la pantalla se apagarán, pero "
"el motor de agua comenzará a funcionar.\n"
"                            </p>\n"
"                            <div class=\"alert alert-danger\" "
"role=\"alert\" >\n"
"                                Antes de cambiar al <b>Modo Manual</b>, "
"verifica que el motor de agua no esté <b>ENCENDIDA</b> mientras esté en "
"<b>Modo Inteligente</b>.\n"
"                                Usa la interfaz web para comprobar su "
"estado. Confirma que el indicador verde <b>LED</b> esté apagado antes de "
"continuar.\n"
"                            </div>\n"
"                            "

