#: templates/manuals/s1.html:431
msgid "Placing the device on the water tank."
msgstr "Colocando el dispositivo en el tinaco."

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:439
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                Place the device sensor as far as "
"possible from the main water inlet of the water tank,\n"
"                                without reaching to much closer to the "
"water tank internal wall, to avoid erroneous\n"
"                                measurements when filling the water tank."
"\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"                                Coloque el sensor del dispositivo lo más "
"lejos posible de la entrada principal de agua del tinaco,\n"
"                                sin acercarse demasiado a la pared "
"interna del tinaco, para evitar mediciones erróneas al llenar el tinaco."
"\n"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:457
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                  Keep in mind that the internal sensor "
"that is placed inside the water tank must have a minimum margin of <b>20 "
"centimeters (AJ-SR04M Sensor)</b>\n"
"                                  from its bottom location to the maximum"
" distance that the water in the tank can reach.\n"
"                                  "
msgstr ""
"                                  Tenga en cuenta que el sensor interno "
"que se coloca dentro del tinaco debe tener un margen mínimo de <b>20 "
"centímetros (Sensor AJ-SR04M)</b>\n"
"                                  desde su ubicación inferior hasta la "
"distancia máxima que el agua en el tinaco puede alcanzar.\n"

msgid ""
"\n"
"                                <p class=\"alert alert-danger my-2\">\n"
"                                   If the tank cannot preserve that "
"minimum distance margin, the sensor blind area is\n"
"                                  reached and erroneous random "
"measurements will be reported.\n"
"                                  Use the <b>RCWL-1670 Sensor</b> if "
"require smaller blind area (2 CM).\n"
"                                </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\">\n"
"                                The installation location may vary "
"depending on the shape of your water tank, how\n"
"                                the lid closes, and its resistance to "
"local conditions. Please choose an installation\n"
"                                method that ensures the device is "
"securely mounted and protected. As this is an experimental device,\n"
"                                the user is responsible for ensuring "
"proper and safe installation.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              "
msgstr ""
"                                <p class=\"alert alert-danger my-2\" >\n"
"                                   Si el tinaco no puede conservar ese "
"margen mínimo de distancia, se alcanzará el área ciega del sensor\n"
"                                  y se reportarán mediciones aleatorias "
"erróneas.\n"
"                                  Use el <b>Sensor RCWL-1670</b> si "
"requiere un área ciega más pequeña (2 CM).\n"
"                                </p>\n"
"                              <p class=\"alert alert-warning my-2\" >\n"
"                                La ubicación de la instalación puede "
"variar dependiendo de la forma de su tinaco, cómo\n"
"                                cierra la tapa y su resistencia a las "
"condiciones locales. Por favor, elija un método de\n"
"                                instalación que garantice que el "
"dispositivo esté montado de forma segura y protegida. Dado que este es un"
" dispositivo experimental,\n"
"                                el usuario es responsable de garantizar "
"una instalación adecuada y segura.\n"
"                              </p>\n"

msgid ""
"\n"
"                              <h4>Placement of the upper Control "
"Unit.</h4>\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-3\">\n"
"                                The control unit can be installed using "
"two main methods, depending on your\n"
"                                specific setup and preferences. Please "
"ensure that the chosen method provides a\n"
"                                secure and stable mounting for optimal "
"performance.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"\n"
"                              <h5>Screw Mounting Method: </h5>\n"
"                              "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                              <h4>Colocación de la Unidad de Control "
"Superior.</h4>\n"
"\n"
"                              <p class=\"my-3\" >\n"
"                                La unidad de control puede instalarse "
"utilizando dos métodos principales, dependiendo de su\n"
"                                configuración específica y preferencias. "
"Por favor, asegúrese de que el método elegido proporcione\n"
"                                un montaje seguro y estable para un "
"rendimiento óptimo.\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"\n"
"                              <h5>Método de Montaje con Tornillos: </h5>\n"

msgid ""
"\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Locate the designated mounting points "
"on the control unit.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Use appropriate screws to securely "
"fasten the unit to a flat surface, such as a wall or a sturdy panel near "
"the water tank.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Ensure the screws are tight and the "
"unit is firmly fixed to avoid movement or detachment over time.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\" >\n"
"                                  Localice los puntos de montaje "
"designados en la unidad de control.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\" >\n"
"                                  Use tornillos adecuados para fijar de "
"forma segura la unidad a una superficie plana, como una pared o un panel "
"resistente cerca del tanque de agua.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Asegúrese de que los tornillos estén "
"apretados y la unidad esté firmemente fijada para evitar movimientos o "
"desprendimientos con el tiempo.\n"
"                                </li>\n"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:512
msgid "Pipe Mounting Method:"
msgstr "Método de Montaje en Tubería:"

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:520
msgid ""
"This method is ideal for installations over a pipe or cylindrical "
"structure with a diameter of approximately 27mm."
msgstr ""
"Este método es ideal para instalaciones sobre una tubería o estructura "
"cilíndrica con un diámetro de aproximadamente 27 mm."

msgid ""
"\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Use the screws, nuts, and mounting "
"accessories provided with the model to securely\n"
"                                  attach the control unit to a pipe of "
"approximately 27mm in diameter.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Ensure the unit is tightly secured and "
"aligned properly to prevent shifting or tilting during operation.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  For the pipe mounting option, inspect "
"the quality of the 3D-printed screws, as they\n"
"                                  may break depending on the print "
"quality, material, or other factors.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\" >\n"
"                                  Use los tornillos, tuercas y accesorios"
" de montaje incluidos con el modelo para fijar\n"
"                                  de manera segura la unidad de control a"
" una tubería de aproximadamente 27 mm de diámetro.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\">\n"
"                                  Asegúrese de que la unidad esté bien "
"sujeta y alineada correctamente para evitar desplazamientos o "
"inclinaciones durante la operación.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\" >\n"
"                                  Para la opción de montaje en tubería, "
"inspeccione la calidad de los tornillos impresos en 3D, ya que\n"
"                                  podrían romperse dependiendo de la "
"calidad de impresión, el material u otros factores.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                "

#: templates/manuals/s1.html:544
msgid ""
"\n"
"                                Regardless of the installation method, "
"always verify that the control unit is\n"
"                                mounted in a location that is safe, "
"stable, and well-protected from adverse\n"
"                                environmental conditions.\n"
"                                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                                Independientemente del método de "
"instalación,\n"
"                                siempre verifique que la unidad de "
"control esté\n"
"                                montada en un lugar seguro, estable y "
"bien protegido\n"
"                                de condiciones ambientales adversas.\n"
"                                "

msgid ""
"\n"
"                              <h4>Positioning the Control Unit for Solar "
"Power</h4>\n"
"                              <p>\n"
"                                If you are using solar power to operate "
"the control unit, it is crucial to position\n"
"                                the device to maximize its exposure to "
"sunlight. Follow these guidelines for\n"
"                                optimal solar performance:\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 list-group-"
"numbered\">\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\"><b>Orientation:</b> Ensure the solar panel is facing the "
"direction that receives the most\n"
"                                  sunlight during the day. In most "
"regions, this means orienting the panel toward\n"
"                                  the south in the northern hemisphere or"
" toward the north in the southern hemisphere.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\"><b>Avoid Obstructions: </b>  Place the control unit in an "
"area free from shadows\n"
"                                  caused by trees, buildings, or other "
"objects that could block sunlight during the day.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\"><b>Regular Maintenance: </b>\n"
"                                  Clean the solar panel periodically with"
" mild soap and water,\n"
"                                  avoiding alcohol or harsh chemicals. "
"Use a soft cloth and rinse thoroughly to remove\n"
"                                  any soap residue, ensuring the panel "
"stays efficient and protected.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                              </ul>\n"
"                              "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                              <h4>Posicionamiento de la Unidad de Control"
" para Energía Solar</h4>\n"
"                              <p>\n"
"                                Si está utilizando energía solar para "
"operar\n"
"                                la unidad de control, es crucial "
"posicionar\n"
"                                el dispositivo para maximizar su "
"exposición\n"
"                                a la luz solar. Siga estas pautas para\n"
"                                un rendimiento solar óptimo:\n"
"                              </p>\n"
"                              <ul class=\"list-group ms-1 list-group-"
"numbered\" >\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\"><b>Orientación:</b> Asegúrese de que el panel solar esté "
"orientado hacia la dirección que reciba la mayor\n"
"                                  cantidad de luz solar durante el día. "
"En la mayoría\n"
"                                  de las regiones, esto significa "
"orientar el panel hacia\n"
"                                  el sur en el hemisferio norte o hacia "
"el norte en el hemisferio sur.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\" ><b>Evitar Obstrucciones: </b> Coloque la unidad de control"
" en un área libre de sombras\n"
"                                  causadas por árboles, edificios u otros"
"\n"
"                                  objetos que puedan bloquear la luz "
"solar durante el día.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                                <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-"
"item-action\" ><b>Mantenimiento Regular: </b>\n"
"                                  Limpie el panel solar periódicamente "
"con\n"
"                                  jabón suave y agua, evitando alcohol o "
"productos químicos agresivos.\n"
"                                  Use un paño suave y enjuague bien para "
"eliminar\n"
"                                  cualquier residuo de jabón, asegurando "
"que el panel\n"
"                                  se mantenga eficiente y protegido.\n"
"                                </li>\n"
"                              </ul>\n"
"                              "

