#: templates/products/r1.html:146
msgid ""
"\n"
"            <b>Remote Pump Control</b><br>\n"
"            <p>The <strong>WiFi Smart Water Pump Controller S1</strong> "
"allows users to remotely manage and operate water pumps using a "
"smartphone or computer.\n"
"                It connects to your existing WiFi network, providing full"
" control and monitoring through an intuitive responsive web app interface"
" from anywhere in the world.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"            <b>Control Remoto de Motor de Agua</b><br>\n"
"            <p>El <strong>Controlador Inteligente de Motor de Agua WiFi "
"S1</strong> permite a los usuarios gestionar y operar motores de agua de "
"forma remota utilizando un smartphone o computadora.\n"
"                Se conecta a tu red WiFi existente, proporcionando "
"control y monitoreo completo a través de una interfaz de aplicación web "
"responsive intuitiva desde cualquier parte del mundo.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"            "

#: templates/products/r1.html:154
msgid "Integration with S1 Sensor"
msgstr "Integración con el Sensor S1"

#: templates/products/r1.html:160
msgid ""
"\n"
"            <p>Designed to seamlessly integrate with the <strong>WiFi "
"Water Level S1</strong>, the controller automatically\n"
"                receives real-time water level data and adjusts pump "
"operations for optimal water management. This ensures\n"
"                efficient automation without the need for manual "
"intervention.</p>\n"
"            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"            <p>Diseñado para integrarse perfectamente con el <strong>WiFi"
" Water Level S1</strong>, el controlador recibe automáticamente\n"
"                datos en tiempo real del nivel de agua y ajusta las "
"operaciones del motor para una gestión óptima del agua. Esto garantiza\n"
"                una automatización eficiente sin necesidad de "
"intervención manual.</p>\n"
"            "

#: templates/products/r1.html:167
msgid ""
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-success active\">\n"
"            <b>Automated Operation</b><br>\n"
"            <p>Equipped with advanced algorithms, the controller "
"automates pump operations based on water\n"
"                level sensor data. Users can configure thresholds and "
"parameters, dictating when the pump should activate\n"
"                or shut off, enhancing efficiency and minimizing manual "
"supervision.</p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary\">\n"
"        <b>Customizable Settings</b><br>\n"
"            <p>Users can define precise thresholds for pump operation, "
"specifying when to start the pump if the\n"
"                water level falls below a set percentage and when to stop"
" it once the tank reaches a defined fill level.\n"
"                Additionally, scheduling and mode adjustments provide "
"flexibility to tailor the system to specific water\n"
"                management needs and conditions, ensuring optimal "
"performance and adaptability.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary active\">\n"
"            <b>No Incoming Flow Detection</b><br>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                As part of its automated operations, the pump can "
"automatically stop if no incoming water flow is detected.\n"
"                This feature is particularly useful for users relying on "
"unstable water sources to fill their tanks,\n"
"                helping to prevent unnecessary motor operation and "
"potential damage.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary\">\n"
"            <b>Pump Compatibility</b><br>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Supports pumps rated for <b>AC 120V or 220V</b>, <b>50/60"
" Hz</b>, with <b>single-phase connection and neutral line</b>.\n"
"                Compatible with pumps up to a <b>maximum of 10 amps</b>. "
"Optional <b>ground connection</b> for added safety.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary active\">\n"
"            <b>External 2.4GHz WiFi Antenna (3dBi or 5dBi)</b><br>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Offers outdoor ranges of <b>100-150 meters</b> with a "
"<b>3dBi</b> antenna and up to <b>200 meters</b> with a <b>5dBi</b> "
"antenna, depending on line-of-sight.<br>\n"
"                Indoors, the range typically spans <b>30-70 meters</b>, "
"influenced by obstacles and antenna choice.\n"
"                Compatible with <b>2.4GHz WiFi</b> range extenders.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary\">\n"
"        <b>Eco-Friendly Design</b><br>\n"
"        <p>The <strong>WiFi Smart Water Pump Controller S1</strong> "
"promotes sustainable water usage by reducing\n"
"            unnecessary pump operation. When paired with the solar-"
"powered <b>WiFi Water Level S1</b>,\n"
"            it creates an eco-friendly water management system that "
"conserves both water and energy.</p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-success active\">\n"
"            <b>Easy-to-Manufacture Design</b>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"               The energy module is integrated into a single PCB. The "
"sensor connects easily via a plug-in,\n"
"                with no soldering required when you purchase the pre-"
"assembled PCB, making it easy for anyone or\n"
"                any factory to manufacture in small batches.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-secondary\">\n"
"        <b>Open Hardware and Software</b><br>\n"
"        <p>With open hardware and software, the controller embraces "
"transparency and innovation.\n"
"            Users have access to its schematics, firmware, and software, "
"allowing for customization and\n"
"            future enhancements. It also integrates with a free version "
"of the cloud service\n"
"            for cost-effective data management.</p>\n"
"\n"
"            <div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9 video-wrapper my-2\">\n"
"              <video autoplay muted loop>\n"
"                <source src=\"https://github.com/rrguardo/WiFi-Smart-"
"Water-Pump-Controller-S1/raw/refs/heads/main/images/CShow1.mp4\" "
"type=\"video/mp4\">\n"
"                Your browser does not support the video tag.\n"
"              </video>\n"
"            </div>\n"
"            "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-success active\">\n"
"            <b>Operación Automatizada</b><br>\n"
"            <p>Equipado con algoritmos avanzados, el controlador "
"automatiza las operaciones del motor basándose en los datos\n"
"                del sensor de nivel de agua. Los usuarios pueden "
"configurar umbrales y parámetros, determinando cuándo el motor debe "
"activarse\n"
"                o apagarse, mejorando la eficiencia y minimizando la "
"supervisión manual.</p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary\" >\n"
"        <b>Ajustes Personalizables</b><br>\n"
"            <p>Los usuarios pueden definir umbrales precisos para la "
"operación del motor, especificando cuándo iniciar el motor si el\n"
"                nivel de agua cae por debajo de un porcentaje establecido"
" y cuándo detenerlo una vez que el tanque alcanza un nivel de llenado "
"definido.\n"
"                Además, la programación y los ajustes de modo brindan "
"flexibilidad para adaptar el sistema a necesidades y condiciones "
"específicas\n"
"                de gestión del agua, asegurando un rendimiento óptimo y "
"adaptabilidad.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary active\">\n"
"            <b>Detección de Falta de Flujo de Entrada</b><br>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Como parte de sus operaciones automatizadas, el motor "
"puede detenerse automáticamente si no se detecta flujo de agua entrante."
"\n"
"                Esta función es especialmente útil para usuarios que "
"dependen de fuentes de agua inestables para llenar sus tanques,\n"
"                ayudando a prevenir operaciones innecesarias del motor y "
"posibles daños.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary\">\n"
"            <b>Compatibilidad con Motores</b><br>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Compatible con motores clasificados para <b>AC 120V o "
"220V</b>, <b>50/60 Hz</b>, con <b>conexión monofásica y línea neutra</b>."
"\n"
"                Compatible con motores de hasta un <b>máximo de 10 "
"amperios</b>. Conexión a <b>tierra opcional</b> para mayor seguridad.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary active\" >\n"
"            <b>Antena WiFi Externa de 2.4GHz (3dBi o 5dBi)</b><br>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"                Ofrece rangos al aire libre de <b>100-150 metros</b> con "
"una antena de <b>3dBi</b> y hasta <b>200 metros</b> con una antena de "
"<b>5dBi</b>, dependiendo de la línea de visión.<br>\n"
"                En interiores, el rango suele ser de <b>30-70 metros</b>,"
" dependiendo de los obstáculos y la elección de la antena.\n"
"                Compatible con <b>extensores de rango WiFi de 2.4GHz</b>."
"\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-primary\">\n"
"        <b>Diseño Ecológico</b><br>\n"
"        <p>El <strong>Controlador Inteligente de Motor de Agua WiFi "
"S1</strong> promueve el uso sostenible del agua al reducir\n"
"            las operaciones innecesarias del motor. Cuando se combina con"
" el <b>WiFi Water Level S1</b> alimentado por energía solar,\n"
"            crea un sistema de gestión de agua ecológico que conserva "
"tanto el agua como la energía.</p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-success active\" >\n"
"            <b>Diseño Fácil de Fabricar</b>\n"
"            <p>\n"
"               El módulo de energía está integrado en una sola PCB. El "
"sensor se conecta fácilmente mediante un conector,\n"
"                sin necesidad de soldadura cuando se compra la PCB "
"preensamblada, lo que facilita que cualquier persona o\n"
"                fábrica lo fabrique en pequeños lotes.\n"
"            </p>\n"
"        </li>\n"
"\n"
"        <li class=\"list-group-item list-group-item-action list-group-"
"item-secondary\" >\n"
"        <b>Hardware y Software Abiertos</b><br>\n"
"        <p>Con hardware y software abiertos, el controlador fomenta la "
"transparencia y la innovación.\n"
"            Los usuarios tienen acceso a sus esquemas, firmware y "
"software, lo que permite personalizaciones y\n"
"            mejoras futuras. También se integra con una versión gratuita "
"del servicio en la nube\n"
"            para una gestión de datos rentable.</p>\n"
"\n"
"            <div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9 video-wrapper my-2\">\n"
"              <video autoplay muted loop>\n"
"                <source src=\"https://github.com/rrguardo/WiFi-Smart-"
"Water-Pump-Controller-S1/raw/refs/heads/main/images/CShow1.mp4\" "
"type=\"video/mp4\">\n"
"                Tu navegador no soporta la etiqueta de video.\n"
"              </video>\n"
"            </div>\n"
"            "

